Indeed this is a maximum and you have a 5 card major. Bid 2@D. Over the forced 2@H response, bid 3N. This tells partner you have exactly 5 hearts and a maximum hand. Remember, 3N is a choice of games. It is NOT a shutout bid. Partner should correct 3N to 4@H with 3+ hearts.|
