This is a slightly trick question. Yes officially you only have 8 HCP. But you must have at least one 8 card major suit fit. Partner cannot have doubletons in both majors. Also, you are entitled to count your shortness which gets your hand up to 11 points using classical point count (2 for singleton, 1 for doubleton). So, I would consider this a maximum and I would bid it as follows:
